g. The authors reviewed and edited the output as needed and\ntake full responsibility for the content of the work.\n\n[16] K. C. Puvvada, N. R. Koluguri, K. Dhawan, J. Balam, and\nB. Ginsburg, “Discrete audio representation as an alternative to\nmel-spectrograms for speaker and speech recognition,” in ICASSP\n2024-2024 IEEE International Conference on Acoustics, Speech\nand Signal Processing (ICASSP).\nIEEE, 2024, pp. 12 111–\n12 115.\n\n9. References\n\n[17] G. Hinton, O. Vinyals, and J. Dean, “Distilling the knowledge in\na neural network,” arXiv preprint arXiv:1503.02531, 2015.\n\n[1] S. Wang, Z. Chen, K. A. Lee, Y. Qian, and H. Li, “Overview\nof speaker modeling and its applications: From the lens of deep\nspeaker representation learning,” IEEE/ACM Transactions on Audio, Speech, and Language Processing, vol. 32, pp. 4971–4998,\n2024.\n[2] B. Desplanques, J. Thienpondt, and K. Demuynck, “Ecapa-tdnn:", "stderr": "\nShell cwd was reset to /inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/iHateTheWorld555.github.io", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-b264d96832e2eace", "type": "tool_result", "content": "\fTable 3: Performance comparison on Vox1 test sets across various bitrates. Results are reported in EER (%) / minDCF format.\nWhile both methods used the ECAPA-TDNN1024 backbone, our model (λ = 40) is trained on Vox2 with the pre-trained teacher from\nWespeaker, and codec-ASV is trained on Vox1+Vox2, so their results are reported on Vox1-O only. (*) indicates the result was reported\nat 18 kbps.\nTest Set\n\n--\nthe experiments on the larger VoxCeleb2 dataset. Table 3 details\nthe results across various bandwidth settings. Compared to the\nresults reported in [14], our approach demonstrates significant\nperformance improvements across tested bitrates. Notably, at\nthe maximum bitrate, our model achieves a 49.5% relative improvement (reducing the EER from 2.08% to 1.05%), closely\napproaching the performance of the teacher model.\nShell cwd was reset to /inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/iHateTheWorld555.github.io", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "74315586-e605-4e80-b1ac-63a94c842af5", "uuid": "6bf62763-fc84-4fe0-957e-1d2476bc1725", "timestamp": "2026-07-11T15:52:12.355Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "\fTable 3: Performance comparison on Vox1 test sets across various bitrates. Results are reported in EER (%) / minDCF format.\nWhile both methods used the ECAPA-TDNN1024 backbone, our model (λ = 40) is trained on Vox2 with the pre-trained teacher from\nWespeaker, and codec-ASV is trained on Vox1+Vox2, so their results are reported on Vox1-O only. (*) indicates the result was reported\nat 18 kbps.\nTest Set\n\n--\nthe experiments on the larger VoxCeleb2 dataset. Table 3 details\nthe results across various bandwidth settings. Compared to the\nresults reported in [14], our approach demonstrates significant\nperformance improvements across tested bitrates. Notably, at\nthe maximum bitrate, our model achieves a 49.5% relative improvement (reducing the EER from 2.08% to 1.05%), closely\napproaching the performance of the teacher model.", "stderr": "\nShell cwd was reset to /inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/iHateTheWorld555.github.io", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "system", "subtype": "task_started", "task_id": "ad7dbef42d2efe663", "tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-a67f3bb8bbe29232", "description": "Wiki + free-search for ASV review", "task_type": "local_agent", "prompt": "I need you to search for background information to help review a paper about Text-Independent Speaker Verification Using Discrete Audio Tokens (arXiv 2607.07579v1). The paper proposes Cross-Feature Knowledge Distillation (CFKD) to improve ASV performance when using neural audio codec (NAC) discrete tokens instead of Fbank features.\n\nPlease perform the following searches and report ALL results (including failures). Do NOT write any code or modify files. Just search and report findings concisely.\n\n1. Try `wiki_query` tool (if available) with these queries:\n   - query: \"speaker verification SOTA baseline\", tags: [\"speech\", \"ASV\"]\n   - query: \"neural audio codec speaker verification\", tags: [\"speech\", \"codec\"]\n   - query: \"knowledge distillation speaker verification\", tags: [\"speech\", \"KD\"]\n   - query: \"discrete audio tokens speaker recognition\", tags: [\"speech\"]\n   - query: \"EnCodec speaker verification performance\", tags: [\"codec\", \"ASV\"]\n\n2. Use the free-search skill or tavily-search skill to search the web for:\n   - \"Codec-ASV neural audio codec speaker verification ICASSP 2025\"\n   - \"DASB discrete audio speech benchmark speaker verification\"\n   - \"knowledge distillation speaker verification embedding 2024 2025\"\n   - \"VoxCeleb speaker verification SOTA 2025 EER\"\n   - \"neural audio codec discrete tokens speaker recognition 2024 2025\"\n\n3. Also try running from /inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/cc-research/my-paper-wiki:\n   - `uv run paper-wiki search --concept \"speaker verification\"`\n   - `uv run paper-wiki search --concept \"knowledge distillation speech\"`\n   - `uv run paper-wiki search --concept \"neural audio codec\"`\n   - `uv run paper-wiki search --dataset \"VoxCeleb\"`\n\nReport all findings concisely. For each search, say whether it succeeded or failed, and summarize the key results. I need to know:\n- What is the current SOTA for VoxCeleb ASV?\n- What prior work exists on codec-based ASV?\n- What prior work exists on KD for ASV?\n- Is the idea of cross-feature KD (Fbank teacher → codec token student) novel?", "uuid": "a5207f38-115f-45d7-8e9b-5b432f3e0d4d", "session_id": "74315586-e605-4e80-b1ac-63a94c842af5"}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "I need you to search for background information to help review a paper about Text-Independent Speaker Verification Using Discrete Audio Tokens (arXiv 2607.07579v1). The paper proposes Cross-Feature Knowledge Distillation (CFKD) to improve ASV performance when using neural audio codec (NAC) discrete tokens instead of Fbank features.\n\nPlease perform the following searches and report ALL results (including failures). Do NOT write any code or modify files. Just search and report findings concisely.\n\n1. Try `wiki_query` tool (if available) with these queries:\n   - query: \"speaker verification SOTA baseline\", tags: [\"speech\", \"ASV\"]\n   - query: \"neural audio codec speaker verification\", tags: [\"speech\", \"codec\"]\n   - query: \"knowledge distillation speaker verification\", tags: [\"speech\", \"KD\"]\n   - query: \"discrete audio tokens speaker recognition\", tags: [\"speech\"]\n   - query: \"EnCodec speaker verification performance\", tags: [\"codec\", \"ASV\"]\n\n2. Use the free-search skill or tavily-search skill to search the web for:\n   - \"Codec-ASV neural audio codec speaker verification ICASSP 2025\"\n   - \"DASB discrete audio speech benchmark speaker verification\"\n   - \"knowledge distillation speaker verification embedding 2024 2025\"\n   - \"VoxCeleb speaker verification SOTA 2025 EER\"\n   - \"neural audio codec discrete tokens speaker recognition 2024 2025\"\n\n3. Also try running from /inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/cc-research/my-paper-wiki:\n   - `uv run paper-wiki search --concept \"speaker verification\"`\n   - `uv run paper-wiki search --concept \"knowledge distillation speech\"`\n   - `uv run paper-wiki search --concept \"neural audio codec\"`\n   - `uv run paper-wiki search --dataset \"VoxCeleb\"`\n\nReport all findings concisely. For each search, say whether it succeeded or failed, and summarize the key results. I need to know:\n- What is the current SOTA for VoxCeleb ASV?\n- What prior work exists on codec-based ASV?\n- What prior work exists on KD for ASV?\n- Is the idea of cross-feature KD (Fbank teacher → codec token student) novel?"}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-a67f3bb8bbe29232", "session_id": "74315586-e605-4e80-b1ac-63a94c842af5", "uuid": "28b9f218-34cd-4a46-8eca-fc8ebbbeb47d", "timestamp": "2026-07-11T15:52:12.359Z"}
